content.description: 1 move wonder that is to the right of nellie crack. The problem starts on a good jug and is a jump to the lip. 1 small foot hold to push off of.
content.location: Located on the same boulder as nellie crack

content.description: Definitely graded because of the first move. The start is at the two lowest crimps and is a dynamic move to a high crimp. High feet are also used.
content.location: The boulder is near the horn problem which is located in a cluster of boulders northeast of the nellie boulder.

content.description: Mantle at the bottom with filler climbing up to the top.
content.location: On the Nellie Boulder on the face right next to Slab #1

content.description: Crux is right off the ground with a technical sequence smearing and with small footholds. Trusting feet in the middle is required and then good jugs for the top out. Crux might be the down-climb the other side.
content.location: Located on the back side of the Nellie Boulder opposite of "Burnt to a Crisp" and "Nellie Boulder Crack"

content.description: Crux is at the start move from the flaky undercling
content.location: Approach the boulder by using a horse trail entrance on either bellermore dr or gantry way and use the trail in the back of the houses

content.description: Boulder is around 3 moves but the hardest is defiantly to the horn.
content.location: From the nellie boulder, head up the mountain and is nestled behind some other boulders

content.description:
This climb is pretty descent. A sit start is used and traverses out right on a nice juggy crack that could also be used as a solid hand jam the climb then converges with the direct crack of the boulder to finish with an easy top out. However, the top out is over a couple of large branches so be careful.

Direct version of the climb is a V0 as well.
content.location: There is o trail that leads to the boulder but is easy to spot from the trail. It is located a little bit up the mountain from the Nellie boulder just above some slabs. Light brush is between the boulder and the boulder.

content.description: Same start as the Nellie Crack with the left hand on an under cling and your right hand on a sloper. Problem goes out right with some stemming and good handholds that have been burnt. Top out over the lip is interesting.
content.location: Same boulder as the nellie crack.
